Three suspected bank robbers have escaped police dragnet in Matuu Town, Machakos County. Yatta sub-county police commander Mary Njoki said the trio suspected to have been on a mission to rob KCB bank, Matuu branch located along Nairobi- Garissa Highway escaped on foot after abandoning a car they were using following a police chase on Tuesday, May 24. "It was reported today by the KCB Matuu branch officials at around 4.30 pm that there were suspicious characters around the bank using a personal vehicle with registration number KCV 969 S, Toyota vitz, silver in colour," Njoki said. "Police rushed to the scene and on arrival, the criminals who were one female and two men sped off to Matuu Town. Police gave them a chase and the suspects abandoned the vehicle," she said. Njoki said the vehicle was impounded at Matuu police station. "The same has been towed to Matuu police station and upon such, one mobile phone was recovered amongst personal clothing belonging to the suspects, " Njoki said. She said police had launched investigations into the matter. "The matter is pending investigation," Njoki said. The incident happened months after armed gangsters robbed a nearby Equity bank, Matuu branch and made away with an unknown amount of money.